HTML attributes are special words used inside the opening tag to control the element's behaviour.
HTML entities are the reserved characters that have special meaning when used in an HTML document. 

Example:
<a href="&#47;users&#47;lyann&#47;followers">
<img class="user-image" src="http:&#47;&#47;adasdasdasd.cloudfront.net&#47;users&# 47;2011&#47;05&#47;24&#47;4asdasd&#47;asdasd.jpg" />
